001package io.github.ai4ci.output;
002
003import io.github.ai4ci.flow.output.CSVWriter;
004
005/**
006 * CommonCSV provides a hierarchical interface structure for CSV output data
007 * models in agent-based simulation systems.
008 *
009 * <p>
010 * Main purpose: define common metadata and execution context shared by the
011 * various CSV record types used across the simulation output pipeline. The
012 * interfaces here form the base contract consumed by CSV and DuckDB writer
013 * implementations.
014 *
015 * <p>
016 * Downstream uses: consumed by {@link io.github.ai4ci.flow.output.CSVWriter}
017 * and {@link io.github.ai4ci.flow.output.DuckDBWriter} implementations and by
018 * exporters in {@link io.github.ai4ci.flow.output.Export} to standardise
019 * exportable records.
020 *
021 * @author Rob Challen
022 */
023
024public interface CommonCSV {
025
026        /**
027         * Execution interface extends Model with experiment execution context. Adds
028         * experiment replica information to track multiple runs.
029         */
030        public interface Execution extends Model {
031                /**
032                 * Get the replica identifier for the execution run.
033                 *
034                 * @return the replica identifier for experiment execution; used to
035                 *         distinguish between independent simulation runs within the same
036                 *         experiment
037                 */
038                int getExperimentReplica();
039        }
040
041        /**
042         * Model interface represents the core simulation model metadata. Extends
043         * CSVWriter.Writeable to ensure CSV serialization capability. Contains basic
044         * model identification and experiment context.
045         */
046        public interface Model extends CSVWriter.Writeable {
047                /**
048                 * Get the experiment name this record belongs to.
049                 *
050                 * @return the experiment name used in the topâ€‘level experiment
051                 *         configuration and exported alongside simulation data
052                 */
053                String getExperimentName();
054
055                /**
056                 * Get the name of the simulation model.
057                 *
058                 * @return the name identifier of the simulation model; typically a short
059                 *         string used to identify the model implementation in exported
060                 *         metadata
061                 */
062                String getModelName();
063
064                /**
065                 * Get the replica index used for the model configuration.
066                 *
067                 * @return the replica identifier for model variation; this is an integer
068                 *         used to distinguish repeated parameter replicates when
069                 *         analysing outputs
070                 */
071                int getModelReplica();
072        }
073
074        /**
075         * State interface extends Execution with time-specific state data.
076         * Represents the complete simulation state at a specific time point. Adds
077         * temporal dimension to the execution context.
078         */
079        public interface State extends Execution {
080                /**
081                 * Get the simulation time step associated with this record.
082                 *
083                 * @return the simulation time step or timestamp; typically an integer
084                 *         representing the discrete time step at which the exported state
085                 *         was recorded
086                 */
087                int getTime();
088        }
089
090}
